Laycon, the Big Brother Naija lockdown 2020 winner, has revealed the first person he is spending his N30 million cash prize on. Recall that Laycon also won other prize monies running into millions from tasks and challenges while in the house. Ogun State Governor, Dapo Abiodun gave him a cheque of N5 million few days ago as well as keys to a new apartment in Ogun State. “The first thing I am going to do with the money is for my mum,” Laycon said in one of media outings at the weekend. “I am certain that the first thing I want to do with the money is for my mum.” Laycon, who said he entered the reality TV show only to promote himself and his song, emerged winner of the 5th edition of BBN with Dorathy coming as first runner-up.